value.Description: This seminar will cover modern research in genome engineering.  Dr. Gelvin will first present a lecture on genome engineering technologies (meganucleases, zinc finger nucleases, TALENs, and CRISPR-mediated genome engineering).  Students will subsequently present assigned papers on the development of these technologies (with an emphasis on CRISPR technology) and their uses.  Examples will come from the animal, plant, and fungal literature.
